# Dataset Schema — Hotel Operations

## Context

LuxurStay Hotels is a major international hotel chain offering hotels for both
business and leisure travellers in major cities across the world. Management has
been receiving complaints about slow room service response times, causing customer
satisfaction to drop below the expected 4.5 rating.

The data covers only requests where customers provided a feedback rating.

---

## Table Relationships

```
service (id) ←── request (service_id)
branch  (id) ←── request (branch_id)
```

---

## Table: `branch`

| Column | Data Type | Nulls / Issues | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | integer | No nulls | Nominal. Unique hotel branch identifier. |
| `location` | text | No nulls in raw | Nominal. One of: EMEA, NA, LATAM, APAC. |
| `total_rooms` | integer | May be NULL or out of range | Discrete. Total rooms in the hotel. Valid range: 1–400. Default: 100. |
| `staff_count` | integer | May be NULL | Discrete. Number of service department staff. NULL → total_rooms × 1.5. |
| `opening_date` | text | `'-'` placeholder present | Discrete. Year hotel opened. Valid range: 2000–2023. Stored as text. |
| `target_guests` | text | `'B.'` and `'Busniess'` typo present | Nominal. Primary guest type: Leisure or Business. |

---

## Table: `request`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | integer | Unique request identifier. |
| `service_id` | integer | Foreign key linking to `service.id`. |
| `branch_id` | integer | Foreign key linking to `branch.id`. |
| `time_taken` | integer | Minutes taken to fulfil the customer request. |
| `request_time` | text | Time period of the request: Day-Peak, Day-Off-Peak, Night. |
| `rating` | integer | Customer satisfaction rating on a 1–5 scale. |

---

## Table: `service`

| Column | Data Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | integer | Unique service identifier. |
| `description` | text | Service type: Meal, Laundry, Cleaning, Other. |

---

## Cleaning Specification (branch table)

| Column | Rule |
|---|---|
| `location` | Apply `UPPER(TRIM())`. Invalid values → `'Unknown'`. |
| `total_rooms` | NULL or outside 1–400 → `100`. |
| `staff_count` | NULL → `ROUND(total_rooms * 1.5)` cast to integer. |
| `opening_date` | `'-'` or NULL → `2023`. Must be valid 4-digit year between 2000–2023. |
| `target_guests` | Only `'Leisure'` and `'Business'` are valid. All others → `'Leisure'`. |
